+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EkbmdVuZJVnRi7ESyRaVei","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I notice a potential issue: in `getBaseContent`, I look for the base version in `theirEntry.versions`, but if main also changed the document, the base version id from the diverge snapshot might only exist in the *current branch's* history, not the source branch's history. The source branch (feature) has the base version since it was cloned from main at creation, but if main also updated the document *after* the branch point, main's history has both old and new versions while feature only has the branch-point-onward versions.\n\nWait — both branches start with a full clone of versions. The base version id is the last version id at branch creation time. That version exists in *both* branches' histories since both got cloned from main at that point. So looking it up in `theirEntry.versions` is correct.\n\nBut there's one issue: when the *current* branch (main) changes a document after the feature branch diverges, the base version is the one *before* main's change. The base version exists in main's history. But I'm looking it up in `theirEntry` (feature branch). That's correct since feature also has a copy of that version. Let me verify with a specific test scenario to make sure the edge case of \"base found in current branch history\" works too:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1080,"cache_read_input_tokens":41325,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1080},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0bff93ce-46df-4569-84bf-79edd3fa9d23","uuid":"29920f98-3a96-4051-a019-d502f77b7941"}
